{"TopicId":156850,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"(Request) TRAPPIST-1 System in KSP","CreatedByName":"MDS_Dan","CreatedById":167816,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-23T02:30:35Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"MDS_Dan","CreatedById":167816,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-23T02:30:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(For anyone that doesn\u0027t know what the title refers to, NASA recently found 7 Earth-size planets orbiting a star ~40 light-years away, press release \u003Ca href=\u0022https://exoplanets.nasa.gov/news/1419/nasa-telescope-reveals-largest-batch-of-earth-size-habitable-zone-planets-around-single-star/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAm I the only one who wants to see this as a mod? Would it be possible to make this a mod using Kopernicus?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022538\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://exoplanets.nasa.gov/internal_resources/538\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Picture for reference)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"juanml82","CreatedById":105344,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-23T03:06:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was going to ask the same thing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DaJay42","CreatedById":108610,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-23T11:56:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u002B1 to that!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.trappist.one/#system\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EHere\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s a web page with all the numbers you need to build the system. It\u0027s quite the crazy (and tiny!) place. The star is only 0.08 Solar masses, while the planets have semi-major axes of 0.01 to 0.06 AU and orbital periods between just 1.5 and 16 days. I image it\u0027d make for a quite fun career.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-02-23T15:19:13Z\u0022 title=\u002202/23/2017 03:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 23, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by DaJay42\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Firemetal","CreatedById":164725,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-23T13:02:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease yes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFire\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-23T19:22:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/153551-protojeb21/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022153551\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/153551-protojeb21/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@ProtoJeb21\u003C/a\u003E Already has you covered \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/155620-122-kopernicus-interstellar-adventure-revived-v110-huge-overhaul-update-19feb17/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2935473\u0026amp;embedComment=2935473\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-2935473\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe says he\u0027s working on the new findings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Firemetal","CreatedById":164725,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-24T13:18:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want a mod that replaces stock planets with Trappist 1. Like Galileo\u0027s Planet Pack and Centauri Dreams. That would be so awesome!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFire\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"electricpants","CreatedById":164151,"CreatedDateT